Name: breast capillary hemangioma
Definition: A breast hemangioma that is characterized by capillary-sized vessels.

Name: breast epithelioid hemangioma
Definition: A breast hemangioma that is characterized by islands and cords on hyalinized and myxoid ground substance as well as intracytoplasmic vacuoles that contain typical erythrocytes and are characterized by fusiform or round nucleated cells.
